OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1781608794
OL,3,CCould extreme weather affect the Fifa
OL,4,CWorld Cup - and how will players cope?
OL,6,FIntense heat and humidity are common
OL,7,Facross the summer months in the United
OL,8,FStates, Mexico, and Canada, where the
OL,9,Ftournament is being held, but
OL,10,Fforecasters are predicting record-
OL,11,Fbreaking temperatures in many places
OL,12,Fthis year.
OL,14,FOfficials are warning that extreme
OL,15,Fheat could put athletes, fans, and
OL,16,Fworkers at risk, especially in July,
OL,17,Fwhich is, on average, the hottest
OL,18,Fmonth of the year for the contiguous
OL,19,FUS, according to the National Oceanic
OL,20,Fand Atmospheric Administration.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30703
